# WiFi Network Finder - ESP32

## Description
Scans and displays available WiFi networks using ESP32.

## Hardware
- ESP32 Dev Board
- USB Cable

## Features
- Scans all nearby WiFi networks
- Shows SSID, signal strength (dBm), and security type

## How to Use
1. Flash firmware to ESP32
2. Open Serial Monitor at 115200 baud
3. Networks will scan every 5 seconds


## Notes
- Add any extra info here

## RSSI RangeQuality
  -30 to -50 dBmExcellent
  -50 to -70 dBmGood
  -70 to -80 dBmFair
  -80 to -90 dBmWeak 
  Below -90 dBmVery Weak

## WIFI MODE
  WiFi.mode(WIFI_AP);   //  Access Point (Server/Host)
  WiFi.mode(WIFI_STA);  // Station (Client)
  WiFi.mode(WIFI_AP_STA); //  Both AP and Client at same time
  WiFi.mode(WIFI_OFF);  // Turn WiFi off
